Requirements:
JavaFX Set-Up

JavaFX Library:
Quelle: https://gluonhq.com/products/javafx/

Make a Path to the Library:
IntelliJ --> Preferences --> Appearance & Behaviour --> Path Variables --> +
--- Name: PATH_TO_FX ---
--- Path: /lib       ---

Add Library to your Project:
File --> Project Structure --> Project Settings --> Libraries --> +/Java (add only the.jar Files)

Change Run Configurations:
Class --> Run --> Edit Configurations --> VM Options:
--module-path ${PATH_TO_FX} --add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml


How to use this Program:
1. Start the ServerApp
2. Enter Port Number and press Connect Button
3. Start ClientAPP
4. Enter the Host and Port Number
(If you run the App from the same PC, the Host is "localhost")
5. Press Connect Button
6. If you want to disconnect, click on File, then disconnect.